Text.Value: I call it the True Soul special.
I am a True Soul. You will treat me with honour.
Clan's on edge - as like to tear a stranger right up.
I'm here to see the sergeant. I have her boots.
I was told to report to the sergeant.
Such insolence. I should take your head for this.
I'll be shagged to Shanatar. Shit's looking up.
Fine - take this. Consider it a goodwill gesture. |XXX gold|
You want in? Pay the toll. You'll slip through like a dagger through dung.
Easy to feed, fat thumbs for digging. Won't find none better.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Morghal peers at player and looks them up and down.

Text.Value: Been wanting a reason to choke the life out of you, shit-for-brains.
A prick-squeak like you should fit right in.
If you weren't clan-sen, I'd put those fat paws to work.
If you weren't a drow-hoon, I'd put those feelers to work.
But your type got their uses. Let's get those meat-paws to work.
I'm here to see the sergeant. I have her boots.
Drugh no. The twat-Soul caused a rockfall. Trapped tighter than a ring on a fat finger.

EditorData.NodeContext: DRUGH NO = FUCK NO. "Droog" like 'good', not 'food'.

Text.Value: Who's the clan-sen, Greymon - another merc for the dig?
Who's the hoon, Greymon - friend of Nere's? Or you plowin' drow now?
Who's the hoon, Greymon - another slave for the dig?
Aye, that he does. Found the hoon sailing Gekh's skiff.
Aye, that she does. Found the hoon sailing Gekh's skiff.
Aye, that they do. Found the hoon sailing Gekh's skiff.
Attack.
You must be joking. I am not giving you a single coin.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Morghal grins evilly and brandishes a blade - then smiles and puts her blade back.

Text.Value: Did I hear right? You keep gnomes as slaves?
You're shitting me. He pay up?
Now go on, sergeant's above. Can't miss her - just follow the screams.
That so?
I am a True Soul. And you will speak with respect.
My reasons for coming are private. Now step aside.
Dry land. My guts'll stop churning now.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The boat arrives and the captain and players disembark.

Text.Value: Greymon, you shithead - time you showed up. We got trouble.
Unclog your hole - just shitting around.
My business is my own. No need to concern yourself with it.
Your Twat-Soul chum owes us a load of coin. You want in? Pay the toll.
But I'm warning you - that twat-Soul ain't settle up soon, there'll be hell to pay for the lot of you cult-buggers.
Aye. He sniffed up Gekh's corpse. Found the hoon sailing his skiff.
Aye. She sniffed up Gekh's corpse. Found the hoon sailing his skiff.
Aye. They sniffed up Gekh's corpse. Found the hoon sailing his skiff.
I was told to report to the sergeant. I have not come to work.
That's the trouble - he got the gold on him. Thrinn's arm's falling off what with the gnome slaves she been beating.
Aye. One of those Absolute crackpots. Found the hoon sailing Gekh's skiff.
Spit it up, Morghal. Or you busy choking on that True Soul Nere's prick with Thrinn?

Synopsis:
Another duergar greets you on the other side of the lake after sailingthere with captain Greymon.

Both duergar are surly, but Morghal in particular. She is suspicious of Absolutists, but happy to take their coin. She should be gruff, and absolutely not listless. She tells you that Nere is trapped above.
